This is a fantastic opportunity, for an established MEP Commercial Manager, to lead the Quantity Surveying and commercial activities on a multi-million pound project. The company concerned are one of the Middle East`s largest MEP Contractors, with an enviable project portfolio. They have been established in the region for over 3 decades, with offices in Dubai, Abu Dhabi, Doha and Riyadh, delivering some of the largest and most innovative projects in the world.The successful candidate will possess the following:- Western educated, ideally with a Degree in Quantity Surveying and MRICS chartered status.- Minimum of 10 years of experience in the MEP Building services industry, holding the position of MEP Commercial Manager, for a minimum of 5 years, on major MEP construction projects.- Proven background in leading large commercial teams within MEP subcontracting organisations.- Experience using FIDIC forms of contract is essential- Excellent communication and negotiating skills, with previous client facing experience.- Must be willing to work a 5 and a half day week.This is an excellent opportunity with fantastic scope for progression and the opportunity to work on some of the finest engineering construction projects in the world.A generous tax free salary, in the region of Ł90-100k (paid locally in Dirhams) inclusive of allowances for accommodation and transport will be provided to the successful candidate. On top of this, you will be entitled to annual performance related bonus, one return ticket to the UK per annum, plus medical cover and local gratuity.For further details and to apply for this position, please contact Nick Booth at Energi People.
